The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The use of random binning and converse technique suggests a focus on probability and statistics, which could also place the paper in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of high-order terms and normal approximation could indicate a machine learning or statistical learning focus, which could place the paper in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
